description:
The Figaro XML Database library is a .NET library that embeds and extends Oracle Berkeley DB XML - the industry-leading, embeddable XML database engine with XQuery-based access to documents stored in containers and indexed based on their content. 

Figaro is a .NET assembly that links into your application, which makes function calls directly to the library, rather than sending messages to a remote server, eliminating the performance penalty of client-server architectures. Figaro is built on top of Oracle Berkeley DB XML and Oracle Berkeley DB, and therefore inherits its rich features and attributes and has no need for human administration. Oracle Berkeley DB XML adds a document parser, XML indexer and XQuery engine on top of Oracle Berkeley DB to enable the fastest, most efficient retrieval of data. Oracle Berkeley DB XML stores data in its native XML format, eliminating the overhead of translating the data.
summary: The Figaro XML Database library is a .NET library that embeds and extends Oracle Berkeley DB XML - the industry-leading, embeddable XML database engine with API and XQuery-based access to documents stored in containers and indexed based on their content. Figaro Data Store (DS) edition supports single threaded reads and writes.

Lykke.MatchingEngine.Connector

Use GoJS to create directed and undirected graphs, network diagrams, flowcharts, workflow diagrams, entity relationship diagrams, BPMN and BPEL applications, organization charts, circuit diagrams, tree diagrams (e.g. syntax trees, sitemaps), data flow diagrams, mindmaps, SCADA diagrams, smart grid applications, planogram tools, UML diagrams and much more. Also supports JSON save and restore, popular automatic graph layout algorithms (tree, layered digraph and force directed), a Palette control for drag and drop of visual components and an Overview control for large diagrams.  

This full featured evaluation does not have a time limit, but there is a watermark in the view.  Purchasing a license is required for deployment.
summary: GoJS is a fast and powerful JavaScript library for implementing interactive diagrams in HTML web applications.
